                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/4838: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-08T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 8, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7760. Have received Algiers 106, December 7, 5 p.m. Mr. Long’s statement<note
                        n="60" xml:id="d395fn60">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rescue of the Jewish and Other Peoples in Nazi-Occupied
                            Territory:</hi> Hearings before the House Committee on Foreign Affairs,
                        78th Cong., 1st sess., on H. Res. 350 and H. Res. 352 (Washington,
                        Government Printing Office, 1943), p. 15. See also <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_228">pp. 228</ref>–<ref target="#pg_238"
                            >238</ref>.</note> referred only in general way to the place of
                    temporary residence center in Africa and is not out of line with the thought in
                    the French draft.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
